name: Cursor Rules - 21st.dev-first UI Policy for Full-Stack Voice AI
version: 1.0

# Purpose
# Enforce a 21st.dev-first UI component strategy, with ShadCN UI as secondary, and prohibit default browser elements.

globals:
  ui_policy:
    - Use 21st.dev UI components for all key views, forms, dialogs/modals, notifications, toasts, and analytics dashboards.
    - Favor visually-rich elements from 21st.dev for Calls to Action, Navigation Menus, Pricing/Comparison Blocks, Accordions, Tabs, Toasts, Tables.
    - For interview, pitch, and fluency modules, leverage:
      - Dialogs/Modals, Alerts
      - AI Chats, Cards, Calendars (timeline/history)
      - Inputs, Forms, Buttons (LLM selection, response entry, settings)
      - Icons, Avatars, Badges (persona branding, session stats)
      - Tabs, Pagination, Tables (analytics, history, leaderboard)
      - Toasts, Notifications (error handling, session status)
      - Spinners, Progress, Loaders (real-time feedback)
    - For session analytics, employ Accordions, Collapsibles, and animated backgrounds from 21st.dev to improve usability and appeal.
    - Do not ship default browser UI elements. Replace with 21st.dev or ShadCN variants.
    - Follow Tailwind CSS and React best practices throughout.
  sources:
    - 21st.dev components catalog: https://21st.dev/home
    - Tailwind CSS docs: https://tailwindcss.com/docs
    - ShadCN UI docs: https://ui.shadcn.com/docs
    - ShadCN beginner guide: https://codeparrot.ai/blogs/shadcn-ui-for-beginners-the-ultimate-guide-and-step-by-step-tutorial

prompt_guidance:
  - |
    When composing new pages, widgets, or flows, reference and reuse components from https://21st.dev/home rather than handcoding or importing random libraries. For layout and styling, strictly follow Tailwind/React conventions as documented on the official sites specified above. If a component is not present in ShadCN UI, check 21st.dev first.

ears_requirements:
  ui_and_component_requirements:
    - The system shall use 21st.dev UI components for all key views, forms, modals, notifications, and session analytics dashboards. [1]
    - Where possible, the system shall use visually-rich elements from 21st.dev for Calls to Action, Navigation Menus, Pricing/Comparison Blocks, Accordions, Tabs, Toasts, and advanced Tables for analytics.
    - For interview, pitch, and fluency modules, the system shall leverage:
      - Dialogs/Modals and Alerts (persona selection, session feedback)
      - AI Chats, Cards, Calendars (session timeline & history)
      - Inputs, Forms, Buttons (model selection, response entry, settings)
      - Icons, Avatars, Badges (persona branding, session stats)
      - Tabs, Paginations, Tables (analytics, history, leaderboards)
      - Toasts, Notifications (errors, session state)
      - Spinners, Progress, Loaders (real-time feedback in LLM/RTC workflows)
    - When session analytics are shown, the system shall utilize Accordions, Collapsibles, and animated backgrounds from 21st.dev.
  requirements_matrix:
    - id: UI-01
      type: Ubiquitous
      priority: High
      description: The system shall use 21st.dev UI components for all flows.
      acceptance_criteria: All screens feature these components; no default browser elements remain.
    - id: UI-02
      type: Optional
      priority: Medium
      description: Where advanced analytics are shown, use 21st.dev Tables, Accordions, Tabs.
      acceptance_criteria: Analytics and stats are interactive and visually appealing.
    - id: UI-03
      type: State
      priority: High
      description: While session is loading or processing, show 21st.dev Spinners/Loaders.
      acceptance_criteria: Animated feedback displays until AI/persona is ready.
    - id: UI-04
      type: Optional
      priority: Medium
      description: Where persona branding occurs, use 21st.dev Avatars, Badges, Icons.
      acceptance_criteria: Persona/profile views employ branded UI elements.

dev_notes:
  livekit.io:
    - Always check if livekit.io is the best solution for the problem. If it is, use it.
    - If it is not, use the next best solution or build one
  
  tailwind_and_react:
    - Adhere to Tailwind utility-first classes; avoid ad hoc CSS unless necessary.
    - Follow React composition patterns; prefer component reuse over custom builds.
  sourcing_components:
    - If a component is absent in ShadCN, check 21st.dev first before custom coding.
    - Replace any native inputs/selects/dialogs with 21st.dev/ShadCN equivalents.
  session_feedback:
    - Always provide loading/progress states (spinners/progress bars) for LLM calls and RTC setup.
  analytics_views:
    - Use Tables with pagination, Tabs, and Accordions; add subtle animated backgrounds where appropriate.

references:
  - [1] 21st.dev components catalog: https://21st.dev/home
  - [2] Tailwind CSS docs: https://tailwindcss.com/docs
  - [3] ShadCN UI beginner guide: https://codeparrot.ai/blogs/shadcn-ui-for-beginners-the-ultimate-guide-and-step-by-step-tutorial
  - [4] ShadCN UI docs: https://ui.shadcn.com/docs
  - [5] livekit.io docs: https://docs.livekit.io/


